                <h5>Weekly Cleaning</h5>
                <p>As much as we all love diamonds, they’re actually magnets for grease. Whenever you touch your diamond, the oil from your hands gets transferred onto the surface of the stone. This can affect its fire and brilliance. To get rid of this grease, you need to soak your diamond jewellery in a solution of warm water with a couple of drops of mild soap. After soaking your jewellery for a while, you can use a clean, new soft toothbrush to gently remove any dirt still on the piece. Make sure you reserve the toothbrush only for your jewellery in the future. Once you’re done gently scrubbing, you can rinse and then wipe your diamond jewellery dry with a lint-free cloth.</p>
                <h5>Storing Jewellery</h5>
                <p>Diamonds, as we all know, are one of the hardest substances known to man. What this means is that one diamond can easily scratch another diamond or even any other gemstone. So it’s important you store each piece of jewellery separately to avoid any unnecessary damage. You can invest in a fabric-lined jewellery box that has individual compartments for each piece of jewellery or you can wrap your diamond jewellery in soft tissue before storing it to keep it safe.
                </p>
